	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=12664><span id= >shyft</span></a><br><span id=notbold>335 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.61]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Me and some friends had these results, levelling exclusively from adventures:<br> - 24 successes, 0 fails. (not so hard at this level to achieve a record like that, if you're twinked even a little. We're twinked quite a LOT hehe, and only needed about a third of the allotted time.)<br> - Didn't hang around after completing missions for extra XP clearing the dungeon. Went on to a new adventure immediately.<br> - Started at level 26; now level 34.<br> - Most adventures yielded 2 AP, then 3 lately, so I have about 55AP.<br><br>I don't think 55AP is really enough for somebody who hasn't been questing for gear from level 26 to 34. So it seems OK to adjust the AP, or the item drops, upward a little at the low end. 50AP for adventures at the high end seems fine.<br><br>The concern about game imbalance, from having massive AP and being able to afford level 65 stuff at level 45, isn't really valid. It's still level 65 stuff; you can't really use it at 45. The way I'm going, hell, when I'm 45 I won't have near enough AP to outfit myself in level 45 gear, much less 65. I'll be able to afford two or three pieces and maybe an aug or two. Good thing I'm a twink!<br><br>Overall I have mixed reviews about LDoN. Twinks rule, as always: the mission must be geared toward &quot;average&quot;, untwinked characters or new players will have zero chance. My level 57 main (untwinked by definition of &quot;main&quot;) has about a 30% success rate, while the twink is blasting through missions in 21 minutes whether there are 5 guys or 6 in the group. It's too hard for untwinked players as it stands, especially in the 45-60 level range. At the same time it's way too easy for twinked players 20-40. Then in the 60's evidently AA points are not factored into mission difficulty so it becomes very easy for some players while remaining too hard for others. Not sure about that assumption on AA points, but from my level-57 point of view it seems to be the case.<br><br>One big complaint is that untwinked players are less popular than ever. With missions that have time limits, they are a burden and can result in a loss. I actually got ridiculed about my gear at the end of one failed mission. Sure, that guy was just a d.i.c.k, but twinkage is more a requirement than an option for LDoN.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Oct&nbsp;&nbsp;7 16:59:47 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
